ed, it can never be, as the eternal one abides within each and every heart forever\n\n- Mimi Novic, The Silence Between the Sighs\n|\nPeople tell you to believe in yourself for your whole life, then call you arrogant when you begin taking their advice.\n\n- Curtis\n|\nIf you can devote yourself to your favorite occupation without getting money for it, but in order to discover your potential, then you will find out who you are\n\n- Sunday\n|\nAmong all the nonsense, mistakes, and bad ideas we come up with, maybe some truth will sneak in.\n\n- Henning Mankell, Sidetracked\n|\nAny other iron on you?” he asked impatiently.“Just my tongue stud.”His look was a mixture of curiosity and horror.“I’m kidding, you idiot. Let’s go.\n\n- Kiersten\n|\nI don't know about your true form, but the weight of your ego sure is pushing the crust of the earth toward the breaking point.\n\n- Jim Butcher, Grave Peril\n|\nA book is a version of the world. If you do not like it, ignore it; or offer your own version in return.\n\n- Salman\n|\nThrough lightest dark or darkest light, You dont need no bling to join the fight. We're mercs with mouths and so much more, Yippee-ki-yay, we're the Deadpool Corps!\n\n- Deadpool\n|\nThis isn't a Christmas special! This is my life. In the real world, miracles and goodness just don't happen.\n\n- Richelle Mead, Frostbite\n|\nI didn't have time to write a short letter, so I wrote a long one instead.\n\n- Mark\n|\nIf you want to know the secret of life, learn with enthusiasm and love with all of your heart.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nThere's a thin line between genius and bottom-barrel stupidness. I hover delicately on a tightrope between the two, wondering where I'll land if I'll ever fall.\n\n- Suzanne Crowley, The Very Ordered Existence of Merilee Marvelous\n|\nI'm bored with that line. I never use it anymore. My new line is 'In 15 minutes everybody will be famous.\n\n- Andy\n|\nWhen you find that a theology has nothing more to offer than what the world already offers, then that theology as a theology is impractical, and therefore, useless.\n\n- Criss Jami, Killosophy\n|\nWhen you live for the purpose of making a difference for the people, for society, for the things that are beyond you, then significance will not be able to elude you.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nSi quieres que tus deseos duren, tienes que pedir algo que te haga feliz y no la felicidad.\n\n- Jackson Pearce, As You Wish\n|\nAll I need is a sheet of paperand something to write with, and thenI can turn the world upside down.\n\n- Friedrich\n|\nWhen things get too complicated, it sometimes makes sense to stop and wonder: Have I asked the right question?\n\n- Enrico\n|\nWhen they cut me open, I want them to say, “Damn! This woman ate well.\n\n- Haylyn Quill, The Delectable Habit of Losing Weight: How to successfully commit to your weight loss goals\n|\nFish for a man, he'll eat for a day, don't teach him to de-bone that fish, You may not have to worry about him tomorrow!\n\n- V.\n|\nLife is a battle of wits between you and the circumstances. Make them, don't let them make you.\n\n- Tapan Ghosh, Faceless The Only Way Out\n|\nThe knowledge that we consider knowledge proves itself in action. What we now mean by knowledge is information in action, information focused on results.\n\n- Peter\n|\nLongfellow smiled. 'A great part of the happiness of life consists not in fighting battles, my dear Lowell, but in avoiding them. A masterly retreat is in itself a victory.\n\n- Matthew Pearl, The Dante Club\n|\nIf you want to know the place, Go see the local book store.\n\n- Mahrukh\n|\nIt doesn’t matter what your area of calling is, if you could invest quality time in it, then, you will be sure to produce the quality amount of products.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, How To Become Great Through Time Conversion: Are you wasting time, spending time or investing time?\n|\nThe older you grow, the younger your fears grow!\n\n- Ernest Agyemang Yeboah, Religion, Philosophy and life\n|\nThe more you get lost in love, the more love you will find to enjoy and appreciate.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nsomehow people forget that there is God....what more to us we're just individuals,,to forget is part of imperfections..\n\n- Orosa\n|\nIn an age in which the media broadcast countless pieces of foolishness, the educated man is defined not by what he knows, but by what he doesn't know.\n\n- Nicolás\n|\nYou are the grim, goal-oriented ones who will not believe that the joy is in the journey rather than the destination no matter how many times it has been proven to you.\n\n- Stephen\n|\nSmartass Disciple: But, you said that it's the truth??Master of Stupidity: O Yes. That is yesterday's truth.\n\n- Toba Beta, Betelgeuse Incident: Insiden Bait Al-Jauza\n|\nBooks, in the plural lose their solidity of substance and become a gas, filling all available space.\n\n- John\n|\nSuccess is a path of setbacks, passion, purpose and inner strength\n\n- Rasheed\n|\nKnowledge is of two kinds. We know a subject ourselves, or we know where we can find information on it.\n\n- Samuel\n|\nUntil then, never lose hope. Never stop loving me. Never forget.  Never Never\n\n- Colleen Hoover, Never Never: Part Two\n|\nAfter all, tomorrow will be prettier than today. It all depends on your choices and actions, and if you are ready to make it.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nIt's a dangerous business, Frodo, going out your door. You step onto the road, and if you don't keep your feet, there's no knowing where you might be swept off to.\n\n- J.R.R. Tolkien, The Lord of the Rings\n|\nThe person who knows his calling will not be embarrassed in front of great and famous people because he knows who he is, and he knows the purpose of his life\n\n- Sunday\n|\nThere are times I wish I were invisible. Which is silly, since I do everything I can to stand out.\n\n- Gena Showalter, Oh My Goth\n|\nOnly bad books have good endings.If a book is any good, it's ending is always bad - because you don't want the book to end.\n\n- Pseudonymous Bosch, The Name of This Book Is Secret\n|\nSweet talk's like salt. You can add some later, if need be, but if you pour out too much, you can't sift it out again.\n\n- Marcia Gruver, Raider's Heart\n|\nAt the root of every form of ungodliness, injustice, nepotism, selfishness, every rivalry and competitive jealousy, is the monster called greed.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\n‪A wise man once said, 'Life is like breathing. If you try to hold it, you'll lose it. But let it come & go & you'll always be connected to it.'‬\n\n- Curtis\n|\nYou can’t destroy knowledge. You can stamp it under and burn it up and forbid it to be, but somewhere it will survive.\n\n- Leigh Brackett, The Long Tomorrow\n|\nThe more I read, the less I know.\n\n- Zeshan\n|\nI am God, la de dah.\n\n- Anne Sexton, The Complete Poems\n|\nWhere there is life, there is hope.\n\n- Alyson Noel, Everlasting\n|\nWhen we take our doubts and questions to Christ, we get truthful answers. We get complete answers. We get the love, wisdom, and support we need.\n\n- Toni Sorenson, Aligned By Christ\n|\nFor this feeling of wonder shows that you are a philosopher, since wonder is the only beginning of philosophy.\n\n- Plato, Theaetetus\n|\nSometimes you can learn, even from a bad experience. By coping you become stronger. The pain does not go away, but it becomes manageable.\n\n- Somaly Mam, The Road of Lost Innocence: The True Story of a Cambodian Heroine\n|\nPolitics determines who has the power, not who has the truth.\n\n- Paul\n|\nI like your mind when it plays with mine. We harmonize, like a dirty sweet symphony.\n\n- Melody  Lee, Moon Gypsy\n|\nIf you wish to know the truth, read the holy Scriptures.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nWhat all good teachers have in common, however, is that they set high standards for their students and do not settle for anything less.\n\n- Marva Collins, Marva Collins' Way\n|\nForeign to knowledge, mystery to senses, alien to emotion: LOVE.\n\n- G